<doc id="1188335" wikidata="Q266645" url="?curid=1188335" title="SideOneDummy Records">
<text>SideOneDummy Records is an independent record label based in Los Angeles. It was founded in 1995 by Bill Armstrong and Joe Sib. The label began as a way for them to release music for their friends&#x27; bands. Thereafter SideOneDummy launched the careers of bands like The Gaslight Anthem, AJJ, Flogging Molly, Gogol Bordello, Title Fight and others. Since 1998, SideOneDummy Records has also released the annual Warped Tour compilation album, which features music by bands playing on the current year&#x27;s tour. Their YouTube channel, which features artists in their current roster, has 116 thousand subscribers and 170,015,900 views (as of February 27, 2025).

