<doc id="1188495" wikidata="Q12157049" url="?curid=1188495" title="Spinuș">
<text>Spinuș () is one of the smallest communes in Bihor County, Crișana, Romania. It is composed of five villages: Ciulești (&quot;Csujafalva&quot;), Gurbești (&quot;Görbesd&quot;), Nădar (&quot;Nadántelek&quot;), Săliște (&quot;Kövesegyháza&quot;), and Spinuș.

It has a population 1,166 people (as of 2021). The Oradea–Brașov highway will pass through this commune in the near future. It is a wine-growing zone.

